  <front>
   <head>To her Grace the Dutchess of Portland, with the foregoing Lines.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">theirs, who but to please aspire,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">On Fiction to employ the Lyre;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Make Gods and Goddesses display</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Splendor of the Nuptial Day.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">paint thee at the hallow'd Shrine,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A solemn, glorious Scene! be Mine;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Now lightly touch'd â€” Some other Hour,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(If e'er the Cloud-dispelling Pow'r</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Remove the Damps, that chill my Vein)</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I'll trace the slight-drawn Lines again;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Warm Col'ring on the Piece bestow,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Till Life shall from the Pencil flow.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bride! with Bliss be crown'd,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Diffusing Happiness around:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beneficent, like , shine;</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Like , grace your Line.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
